16/03/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Foreign Ministry filed a formal protest note with the Greek Foreign Ministry over the conduct of Greek soldiers caught on videotape chanting insults against Macedonia.
Greek Ambassador to Macedonia Theodora Grosomanidou was handed the note on Thursday (March 15th).
Macedonian authorities urged Athens to denounce the incident, which occurred during a military exercise in October 2005.
The footage aired this month on Greek television.
In other news Thursday, Macedonian and NATO officials signed a memorandum providing for the town of Ohrid to host a NATO security forum between June 28th and 29th.
The event would involve over 800 officials from 49 countries, including NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer.
(Utrnski Vesnik - 16/03/07;
MIA, Makfax, A1 TV, AFP - 15/03/07)
